content:
# Grid

* Comprised by Columns, rows, Gutter, Margins


:::tip success
Turn on the grid functionality on dev tools for better visual
::: 


# Container
:::note 
The container will make itself bigger to fit the items if they overflow the size.
::: 


### Rows and Columns Template
> - grid template columns 
> - grid template rows

```sass
 /* Define Template - Unequal Values*/
    grid-template-rows: 100px 100px 300px;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 2fr;


 /* Define Template - Equal Values */
    grid-template-rows: repeat(3, 100px);
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 3fr);
```
### Rows and Columns Template Shorthand

> - grid-template

```sass
 /* Define Template Shorthand Rows/Columns */
    grid-template: repeat(3, 100px) / repeat(3, 3fr);

 /* Define Template Shorthand Rows/Columns */
    grid: repeat(3, 100px) / repeat(3, 3fr);
```


### Gutter Gap

:::note
The gutter gap could cause the items to overflow the container if 1fr is not used.
::: 

> - gap

```sass
/* Set Gutter */
    gap: 5px;
```

### Template Areas 

> -  grid-template-areas:

```sass
/* Set Template Area Inside Container */
 grid-template-areas:
      "hd hd hd hd   hd   hd   hd   hd   hd"
      "sd sd sd main main main main main main"
      ".  .  .  ft   ft   ft   ft   ft   ft";

 /* Assign Template Area Inside Item */
    grid-area: hd;
```


### Implicit Rows and Columns

> - grid-auto-rows
> - grid-auto-columns

```sass
/* If additional rows or columns are added set the size to 50px*/
  grid-auto-rows: 50px;
  grid-auto-columns: 50px;
```


### Implicit Rows and Columns Direction

> - grid-auto-flow

```sass
/* new items render as columns*/
  grid-auto-flow: column;
```






# Items



### Grid Column

> - grid column start
> - grid column end
> - grid column


```sass
/* Define Column Span */
   grid-column-start: 1;
   grid-column-end: 4;

/* Define Column Span Shorthand*/
   grid-column: 1 / 4;
```


### Grid Row

> - grid row start
> - grid row end
> - grid row

```sass
/* Define Row Span */
   grid-row-start: 1;
   grid-row-end: 4;

/* Define Row Span Shorthand*/
   grid-row: 1 / 4;
```


### Grid Area


> - grid area

```sass
 /* Start at row 2 and end at row 4, Start at column 2 and end at column 3*/

  grid-area: 2/ 2 / 4 / 3;
```


### Overlapping Elements

> - z-index

```sass
 /* If the element in the Grid Area Overlaps just set its z Indez */
   z-index: 5;
```






# Responsiveness

- autofit
- min max

```sass
 /* autofit Minimum 200px Max 1 Fraction of available space*/
grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
```
